 {"id": "franken_networkx-algconnkwargs", "title": "REVIEW: [LOW] algebraic_connectivity missing tol/method/seed kwargs", "description": "nx.algebraic_connectivity exposes tol/method/seed for its iterative Fiedler solver. fnx accepted only (G, weight, normalized). Added the kwargs for API parity; the bespoke Python impl uses np.linalg.eigvalsh so the iterative knobs are accepted but dont alter numerics (future native-port work).", "status": "closed", "priority": 4, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T12:09:48.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T12:09:48.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T12:09:48.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Added kwargs for signature parity", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-dagltie", "title": "REVIEW: [LOW] dag_longest_path on disconnected DAG picks wrong component", "description": "On a disconnected DAG with multiple equal-length maximum paths, nx picks the longest path in the insertion-order first component. fnx Rust fast-path could pick a later-inserted component. Delegate to nx for disconnected DAGs (detect via is_weakly_connected); keep Rust fast-path for the common connected case.", "status": "closed", "priority": 4, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T12:14:21.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T12:14:21.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T12:14:21.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Delegate for disconnected DAGs", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-nonenode", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] fnx accepted None as node key; nx rejects", "description": "nx.Graph.add_node(None) raises ValueError(\"None cannot be a node\"). fnx silently accepted None (with confused has_node(None) vs has_node(\"None\") behavior since the Rust key layer stringifies). Added Python edge-guards on add_node/add_edge for all 4 graph classes rejecting None with the nx-exact error.", "status": "closed", "priority": 3, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T12:14:21.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T12:14:21.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T12:14:21.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Python guards on add_node/add_edge across all 4 classes", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-bulkgen", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] 11 algorithm functions returned list instead of generator", "description": "nx contract: find_cliques, find_cliques_recursive, enumerate_all_cliques, all_simple_paths, all_shortest_paths, bfs_edges, dfs_edges, bfs_layers, isolates, minimum_spanning_edges, maximum_spanning_edges all return generators. fnx returned materialised lists. User code calling next(iter) TypeErrored. Wrapped each at module init to return an iterator. Updated 10 existing tests that encoded the list contract.", "status": "closed", "priority": 3, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T12:20:29.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T12:20:29.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T12:20:29.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Bulk-promote via iter() wrapper at module init", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
